	   <tr><td colspan=2>As of yesterday this quest is working again!!!&nbsp;&nbsp;We took Fegul with a 46 ranger, 45 bard and myself, 46 druid.  I'd say he's a bit tougher than the elites.  The ranger didn't make it. :(  Fergul took a snare quite nicely but keeping him rooted was problematic.  <br><br>Not sure about the BM spawn time, she was back up an hour or so after i completed the quest.<br><br>The best approach IMHO is to have the harness giver follow the BM as she wanders around on her way to the fort with the rest of your party waiting at Fergul's spawn point (the fort gate on the EW zone side).  <br><br>As a side note...  When I do this quest again for my ranger partner, we'll do it late at night.  Within 30 seconds of announcing I was doing the quest and handing in the harness, I was getting spammed by people threatening to KS because I &quot;stole&quot; their quest.  Even though I was the only one even in the shardwurm cave when I handed in the harness and there had been no shouts or OOC's that anyone else was attempting it.  Next time will be late night when the children are asleep  :)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Feb 18 13:36:21 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
